<TITLE> 'Power supply suffers on lack of transmission lines' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 23 (bdnews24.com)Power supply was being hampered at places due to lack of transmission lines despite generation, the state minister for power said ion Saturday. "When we assumed power we had said that we would be able to produce 741 MW electricity by July. We have already generated more than 741 MW of power," Shamsul Haque Tuku said at a discussion on power at the Institution of Diploma Engineers in the capital. "But, we cannot provide to diverse places due to lack of transmission lines." "I started work with 3200 MW power, but the production has reached 4162 MW," the junior minister said. He also claimed that power production does not go down below 3700-3800 MW any day. Tuku touched on government plans to generate power at regional level. He observed that gas and coal are not being extracted for various reasons. The Power Grid Company of Bangladesh hosted the discussion. b
